      <div class="faq-list reveal">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How long does SEO take to show results?</summary>
          <p>SEO usually starts showing early movement within 2 to 3 months, while stronger ranking, traffic, and lead improvements often build over 4 to 6 months depending on your competition, website condition, and content strength.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is included in your SEO services?</summary>
          <p>Our SEO services can include technical SEO audits, on-page optimization, local SEO, content planning, internal linking, schema direction, performance fixes, competitor analysis, and ongoing reporting focused on rankings, traffic quality, and conversions.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do you offer local SEO for businesses targeting nearby customers?</summary>
          <p>Yes. We help improve local visibility through Google Business Profile optimization, location pages, local keyword targeting, citation consistency, and strategies designed to increase map pack and nearby search visibility.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can SEO help generate more leads and sales, not just traffic?</summary>
          <p>Yes. Our SEO work is built around commercial intent, stronger landing pages, and conversion-focused structure so your website attracts more qualified visitors and turns that traffic into enquiries, leads, and sales opportunities.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do you measure SEO performance?</summary>
          <p>We track rankings, impressions, organic traffic, landing page growth, technical improvements, user engagement, lead quality, and conversions so performance is measured by business impact instead of vanity metrics alone.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is SEO worth it for a new website or a redesigned website?</summary>
          <p>Yes. SEO is especially valuable during a new launch or redesign because it helps build the right site structure, keyword targeting, page hierarchy, and technical foundation early, which supports faster and more sustainable growth later.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
